  "texts": [
    "S col.1 included 65 user utterances for Experiment 1, 82 6W1H needs for Experiment 2, and 50 keywords for Experiment 3.",
    "The SUCCEED system used in Experiment 3 contained 140 registered cases.",
    "Experimental ResultIn Experiments 1 and 2, the framework G-Eval was used to evaluate the input and output of natural language generation (NLG) based on specified metrics [27].",
    "Since natural language is inherently human-centered, the most accurate evaluation of NLG processes is typically done manually by multiple human experts.",
    "G-Eval, however, leverages LLMs to evaluate NLG processes, and experiments have shown that high-performance LLMs can perform evaluations that closely resemble those of humans."
